ABUJA – The coronavirus pandemic worsens in Nigeria with the disease spreading to Rivers State, where the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) said one case has been confirmed in the state. In all, the NCDC announced on its Twitter handle @NCDCgov late on Wednesday night that five more cases had been confirmed bringing the total number of confirm cases in Nigeria to 51 as at 11.25pm. The statement said among the five new cases, three were returning travellers while two are close contacts of a confirmed case. Furthermore, it said two new confirmed cases were in Abuja, two in Lagos and one in Rivers. The Tweet reads: Five new cases of #COVID19 have been confirmed in Nigeria: 2 in FCT, 2 in Lagos & 1 in Rivers 3 are returning travellers into Nigeria & 2 are close contacts of a confirmed case As at 11:25 pm 25th March, there are   51 confirmed cases  2 discharged 1 death https://t.co/DmJ47wntZ6  The PUNCH reports that the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control on Sunday said 30 cases have now been confirmed in the country. In the update posted on its website, the centre said Abuja, which had one case in the morning of Sunday, now have four cases. It said Ekiti has… March 23, 2020 In "News" The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control on Tuesday announced two new cases of the novel coronavirus increasing the confirmed cases in the country to 46. One of the two new cases was confirmed in Lagos State with the other case in Osun State, its first case. The centre said both… March 25, 2020 In "News" By Jessica Onyegbula Abuja - The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on Friday confirmed that 275 cases of Lassa fever were recorded since its outbreak in parts of the country. This was made known in a statement by the Chief Executive Officer, NCDC, Dr Chikwe Ihekweazu, in Abuja. Ihekweazu… February 8, 2019 In "News"